revision.text:
The '''Architectural Conservation Award''' ({{lang-th|รางวัลอนุรักษ์ศิลปสถาปัตยกรรมดีเด่น}}) is given by the [[Association of Siamese Architects]] in recognition of [[architectural conservation]] efforts by both the public and private sectors in [[Thailand]]. The awards, first given in 1982 and held annually since 2004, are presented to multiple winners in three categories, namely: buildings, people/organizations, and vernacular communities.
